%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adtech%20execs%20keep%20leaving.%20It's%20the%20sign%20of%20a%20new%20era.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223577%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Revolving%20door%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F55773efd6da811203cf682e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222703%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20say%20the%20revolving%20door%20of%20adtech%20startups'%20top%20ranks%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20as%20investors%20push%20for%20profit%20and%20scale.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2F%20Brendan%20McDermid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAdtech%20startups%20face%20leadership%20changes%20as%20investors%20demand%20growth%20and%20profitability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%20are%20looking%20for%20adtech%20startups%20to%20achieve%20scale.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECTV%20and%20retail%20media%20offer%20growth%2C%20but%20challenges%20remain%20with%20margins%20and%20competition.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EClose%20observers%20of%20the%20adtech%20industry%20will%20have%20noticed%20there's%20been%20a%20heap%20of%20change%20in%20the%20upper%20ranks%20of%20the%20sector's%20startups%20in%20recent%20months%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-firms-investing-in-advertising-and-marketing-companies-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinanced%20by%20private%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xr.global%2Fpress-releases%2Fxr-announces-strategic-leadership-changes-to-accelerate-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELouisa%20Wong%20stepped%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20chief%20executive%20of%20Gamut%20Capital-owned%20XR%20Xtreme%20Reach%20in%20August.%20She%20was%20replaced%20in%20the%20interim%20by%20Chandler%20Bigelow%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20financial%20officer.%20Doug%20Knopper%2C%20an%20investor%20in%20the%20company%2C%20was%20appointed%20executive%20chairman%2C%20while%20adtech%20veteran%20Jo%20Kinsella%20was%20promoted%20to%20global%20president%20and%20chief%20operating%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adexchanger.com%2Fonline-advertising%2Ftriplelift-ceo-dave-clark-abruptly-exits-after-setting-the-ssp-on-a-new-trajectory%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDave%20Clark%20left%20his%20role%20as%20chief%20executive%20of%20Triplelift%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20responsibilities%20were%20split%20among%20an%20%26quot%3Boffice%20of%20the%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20led%20by%20Eric%20Roza%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20its%20lead%20investor%2C%20Vista%20Equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2Fpro%2Fmedia-deals%2F2024%2F01%2F04%2Fvideoamp-ceo-out-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVideoAmp%20CEO%20Ross%20McCray%20exited%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20passing%20the%20reins%20to%20board%20member%20and%20investor%20Peter%20Liguori%2C%20now%20executive%20chairman.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2024%2F10%2F01%2Fvideoamp-media-measrement-nielsen-sale%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAxios%20reported%20this%20month%2C%20citing%20multiple%20sources%2C%20that%20the%20company%20is%20now%20pursuing%20a%20sale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20its%20investor%20Vista%20Credit%20Partners%20reportedly%20leading%20some%20of%20those%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20changes%20comes%20with%20its%20own%20company-specific%20nuance%2C%20but%20experts%20said%20there%20are%20broader%20industry%20trends%20that%20link%20them.%20Those%20experts%20%E2%80%94%20bankers%2C%20adtech%20executives%2C%20and%20consultants%20%E2%80%94%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20revolving%20door%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20over%20the%20next%20six%20months%20as%20investors%20press%20adtech%20companies%20for%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20marks%20the%20next%20stage%20of%20evolution%20for%20the%20adtech%20industry.%20With%20the%20digital%20ad%20market%20largely%20dominated%20by%20tech%20giants%20Google%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Meta%2C%20independent%20adtech%20companies%20are%20forced%20to%20find%20new%20ways%20to%20compete%20over%20the%20remaining%20scraps.%20The%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20startups%20still%20duking%20it%20out%20are%20now%20entering%20their%20operator%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAutomation%2C%20AI%2C%20and%20the%20optimization%20of%20corporate%20structures%20will%20mean%20that%20only%20the%20lean%2C%20mean%20companies%20are%20going%20to%20end%20up%20gaining%20market%20share%20and%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Karl%2C%20chief%20business%20development%20officer%20at%20the%20M%26amp%3BA%20advisory%20firm%20JEGI%20Clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd8233e1-0d16-4bc2-8b40-8db1559a0af4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdtech%20valuations%20have%20come%20back%20down%20to%20earth%2C%20but%20PE%20investors%20still%20want%20scale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%20such%20as%20Vista%2C%20GTCR%2C%20and%20Blackstone%20have%20been%20increasingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-firms-investing-in-advertising-and-marketing-companies-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eactive%20investors%20in%20the%20adtech%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20a%20flurry%20of%20deals%20between%202021%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20784%20PE%20or%20PE-sponsored%20transactions%20in%20the%20media%20and%20marketing%20space%20in%202021%2C%20up%2096%25%20from%20the%20prior%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20advisory%20firm%20Ciesco.%20That%20number%20rose%20to%20874%20in%202022%20and%20lowered%20slightly%20to%20786%20in%202023%2C%20per%20Ciesco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20a%20few%20years%20have%20passed%2C%20and%20leadership%20changes%20are%20to%20be%20expected%2C%20given%20historic%20PE%20investment%20cycles%2C%20said%20Mark%20Wright%2C%20a%20veteran%20tech%20investor%20and%20executive%2C%20who%20now%20leads%20the%20M%26amp%3BA%20strategic%20advisory%20practice%20at%20Prohaska%20Consulting.%20Founding%20teams%20make%20way%20for%20more%20experienced%20operators%20who%20can%20take%20the%20company%20to%20the%20next%20level%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20there%20are%20exceptions%20to%20the%20rule%2C%20there%20are%20very%20few%20founding%20teams%20that%20are%20marvelous%20at%20groundbreaking%20innovation%20that%20can%20successfully%20make%20the%20transition%20to%20managing%20and%20operating%20at%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20and%20private%20valuations%20of%20adtech%20companies%20have%20dropped%20dramatically%20since%202021%2C%20the%20height%20of%20the%20zero-interest-rate%20period%20when%20there%20was%20a%20rise%20in%20digital%20ad%20spending%20and%20a%20slew%20of%20adtech%20IPOs.%20Tougher%20macroeconomic%20conditions%20in%20the%20years%20since%20put%20a%20strain%20on%20consumer%20spending%20and%20marketing%20budgets%2C%20cooling%20the%20markets%20and%20M%26amp%3BA%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20changes%20you're%20seeing%20are%20indicative%20of%20a%20two-year%20cycle%20post-COVID%20where%20things%20are%20back%20to%20normal%2C%20or%20the%20new%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20Karl%20of%20JEGI%20Clarity%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20company%20performance%20could%20be%20tied%20to%20events%20that%20were%20out%20of%20their%20control%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20that%20excuse%20no%20longer%20suffices.%20Investors%20want%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeeting%20growth%20expectations%20has%20been%20a%20challenge%20for%20some%20companies.%20JEGI%20Clarity%2C%20which%2C%20alongside%20CIL%20Management%20Consultants%2C%20conducted%20a%20survey%20of%2025%20marketing%20services%20agency%20leaders%20this%20summer%2C%20heard%20from%20multiple%20CEOs%20who%20said%202022%20and%202023%20were%20some%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20operating%20environments%20of%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20surveyed%20said%20they%20were%20more%20optimistic%20about%202024%20now%20that%20rates%20have%20stabilized%20and%20clients%20are%20less%20risk-averse%20with%20their%20marketing%20budgets.%20Almost%20three-quarters%20(70%25)%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20study%20said%20that%20their%20margins%20had%20remained%20stable%20or%20increased%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a33b071-67d8-4249-828a-d18e4d17a037%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECTV%20is%20adtech's%20bright%20spot%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it's%20complicated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20rising%20global%20advertising%20market%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20surpass%20%241%20trillion%20in%20spending%20next%20year%2C%20not%20all%20adtech%20vendors%20are%20positioned%20to%20reap%20the%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20connected%20TV%20space.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20ad%20channels%20in%20the%20US%2C%20with%20spending%20expected%20to%20grow%2013.3%25%20and%20cross%20%2430%20billion%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20Emarketer.%20The%20change%20in%20viewing%20patterns%20and%20forecast%20ad%20spend%20attracted%20investor%20interest%20in%20adtech%20companies%20that%20had%20a%20strong%20position%20in%20CTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221410%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emarketer%20US%20TV%20CTV%20ad%20spend%20chart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6702b2923f2165d716debbe0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConnected-TV%20ad%20spending%20is%20expected%20to%20cross%20%2430%20billion%20in%20the%20US%20this%20year%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20space%20with%20relatively%20low%20margins%20for%20most%20adtech%20vendors.%3Cp%3EEmarketer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20much%20of%20the%20recent%20growth%20in%20CTV%20advertising%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20platforms%20like%20YouTube%20and%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video%20%E2%80%94%20so-called%20walled%20gardens%20that%20don't%20integrate%20third-party%20adtech%20vendors%20such%20as%20buying%20platforms%20and%20exchanges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECTV%20is%20also%20a%20lower-margin%20channel%20for%20adtech%20vendors%20than%20traditional%20online%20display%2C%20where%20up%20to%20half%20of%20every%20dollar%20spent%20on%20ads%20gets%20gobbled%20up%20by%20vendors%20like%20demand-side%20platforms%2C%20ad%20exchanges%2C%20ad%20servers%2C%20measurement%20vendors%2C%20and%20data%20brokers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20network%20TV%2C%20those%20supply%20chain%20costs%20are%20in%20the%2015%25%20level%20%E2%80%94%20you%20have%20to%20take%2050%25%20and%20squeeze%20it%20down%20to%2015%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Prohaska's%20Wright%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20put%20a%20real%20emphasis%20on%20operating%20at%20scale%20and%20put%20a%20pressure%20on%20margins.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20TV%20viewing%20grew%20fragmented%2C%20several%20adtech%20companies%20that%20took%20on%20investment%20in%20recent%20years%20positioned%20themselves%20as%20rivals%20to%20ratings%20giant%20Nielsen.%20These%20firms%20are%20jockeying%20to%20become%20the%20go-to%20companies%20for%20tracking%20audiences%20or%20to%20become%20the%20universal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adexchanger.com%2Fadexplainer%2Fadexplainer-tv-measurement-vs-tv-currency%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrency%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20to%20buy%20TV%20and%20video%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Nielsen%20still%20hasn't%20been%20unseated.%20And%20Walmart's%20acquisition%20of%20TV%20manufacturer%20Vizio%20%E2%80%94%20from%20which%20many%20adtech%20vendors%20license%20viewing%20data%20derived%20from%20its%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20TV%20sets%20%E2%80%94%20could%20signal%20further%20trouble%20ahead%20if%20the%20grocery%20giant%20doesn't%20renew%20those%20contracts%20when%20they%20expire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Walmart-Vizio%20deal%20front%20of%20mind%2C%20adtech%20companies%20and%20investors%20are%20likely%20to%20turn%20their%20attention%20to%20retail%20media%2C%20where%20ads%20are%20placed%20on%20e-commerce%20sites.%20Retail%20media%20is%20also%20growing%20at%20a%20clip%2C%20with%20almost%20every%20retailer%20and%20app%20owner%20now%20also%20operating%20an%20ad%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20complexity%20for%20advertisers%20offers%20opportunities%20for%20adtech%20companies%20to%20innovate.%20Though%2C%20while%20around%20%241%20in%20every%20%247%20US%20ad%20dollars%20is%20expected%20to%20go%20to%20the%20space%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Emarketer%2C%20retail%20media%20is%20largely%20dominated%20by%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20some%20executive%20shuffling%20happening%20in%20the%20retail%20media%20ranks%3A%20Megan%20Clarken%2C%20who%20leads%20the%20publicly%20traded%20adtech%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigiday.com%2Fmedia-buying%2Fcriteo-seeks-new-chief-executive-after-megan-clarken-announces-pending-exit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECriteo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20she%20plans%20to%20step%20down%20within%20the%20next%20year%20once%20her%20successor%20is%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20industry%20observers%20expect%20more%20adtech%20management%20upheaval%20ahead%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20further%20consolidation%20of%20the%20sector%20once%20the%20intense%20fourth-quarter%20holiday%20period%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20will%20see%20more%20heavy-handed%20PE%20involvement%20primarily%20because%20the%20M%26amp%3BA%20market%20hasn't%20been%20great%20and%20people%20sat%20on%20the%20sidelines%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Domenic%20Venuto%2C%20COO%20of%20investment%20bank%20Progress%20Partners%20and%20soon-to-be%20chief%20of%20product%20and%20data%20at%20media%20agency%20Horizon%20Media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20can%20only%20sustain%20so%20many%20of%20these%20companies%20that%20have%20grown%20to%20be%20quite%20sizable%20but%20are%20now%20hitting%20their%20upper%20limits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%2