ng%20Banana%20Waste%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBorn%20into%20a%20farming%20family%2C%20Jagat%20Kalyan%20spent%20his%20childhood%20playing%20in%20the%20lush%20green%20fields%20of%20Hajipur%2C%20Bihar.%20He%20saw%20his%20family%20toil%20day%20and%20night%20to%20cultivate%20banana%20trees%2C%20but%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20harvested%20the%20fruit%2C%20the%20tree%20was%20axed%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20takes%20about%20nine%20months%20to%20grow%20bananas%2C%20and%20once%20the%20fruits%20are%20harvested%2C%20farmers%20need%20to%20chop%20down%20the%20tree%20as%20it%20produces%20fruits%20only%20once%20in%20its%20life%20cycle.%20I%20would%20see%20piles%20of%20banana%20trees%20dumped%20as%20waste%20in%20a%20corner%20of%20the%20field.%20Clearing%20the%20field%20also%20becomes%20a%20headache%20for%20farmers%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20reveals%20that%20India%20leads%20the%20world%20in%20banana%20production%20with%20an%20annual%20output%20of%20about%2014.2%20million%20tonnes.%20After%20harvesting%2C%20almost%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8434441%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%20percent%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20banana%20biomass%20is%20left%20as%20waste!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jagat%20and%20his%20friends%20utilise%20banana%20tree%20waste%20by%20converting%20it%20into%20yarns%2C%20folders%2C%20paintings%2C%20and%20much%20more.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367841%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJagat%20and%20his%20friends%20utilise%20banana%20tree%20waste%20by%20converting%20it%20into%20yarns%2C%20folders%2C%20paintings%2C%20and%20much%20more.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJagat%20did%20not%20have%20a%20solution%20to%20this%20issue%20until%202021%20when%20he%20recognised%20this%20inefficiency%20in%20the%20agricultural%20process%20and%20decided%20to%20turn%20waste%20into%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20his%20zero-waste%20startup%2C%20Taruwar%20Agro%2C%20he%20utilises%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F304140%2Fmba-graduate-turns-banana-stem-waste-into-natural-fibre-eco-friendly-handicraft-earns-lakhs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanana%20tree%20waste%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20converting%20it%20into%20banana%20fibre%2C%20which%20eventually%20serves%20as%20a%20raw%20material%20for%20various%20products%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20handicrafts%2C%20yarns%2C%20sanitary%20pads%2C%20and%20banana%20leather.%20By%20turning%20this%20waste%20into%20wealth%2C%20he%20has%20established%20a%20multi-lakh%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20college%20friends%20to%20co-founders%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20his%20engineering%20and%20MBA%2C%20Jagat%20secured%20a%20job%20at%20a%20startup%20that%20focused%20on%20climate%20change%20and%20the%20environment.%20After%20working%20for%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20he%20received%20various%20job%20offers%20from%20companies%20in%20Tanzania%20and%20Dubai.%20Instead%20of%20accepting%20these%20opportunities%2C%20Jagat%20aspired%20to%20run%20his%20own%20sustainable%20company%20in%20his%20native%20state%20of%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20job%20was%20very%20demanding%20and%20we%20were%20required%20to%20work%20for%2010%20to%2012%20hours.%20I%20would%20often%20discuss%20with%20my%20college%20friends%20Satyam%20Kumar%20and%20Nitish%20Verma%20about%20quitting%20jobs%20to%20build%20something%20meaningful%20of%20our%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20Jagat%20and%20his%20college%20friends%20started%20researching%20various%20issues%20that%20needed%20their%20attention.%20%E2%80%9CThrough%20our%20work%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20put%20Bihar%20on%20the%20world%20map.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20it%20hit%20us%20that%20since%20Hajipur%20is%20known%20for%20its%20banana%20production%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20focus%20on%20banana%20waste%20%E2%80%94%20an%20issue%20that%20all%20of%20us%20grew%20up%20seeing%20on%20our%20fields%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22After%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367842%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAfter%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20shape%20their%20dreams%20into%20reality%2C%20the%20trio%20quit%20their%20jobs%20and%20launched%20Taruwar%20Agro%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20innovative%20approach%20focuses%20on%20converting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F310086%2Fmba-graduate-mehul-shroff-sustainable-startup-turns-banana-waste-into-ecofriendly-craft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanana%20waste%20%3C%2Fa%3Einto%20valuable%20products%2C%20contributing%20to%20environmental%20sustainability%20and%20creating%20economic%20opportunities%20for%20local%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20sources%20banana%20waste%20from%20at%20least%2030%20local%20farmers.%20%E2%80%9CDepending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20tree%2C%20we%20pay%20Rs%205%20and%20Rs%2025%20per%20tree.%20Now%2C%20they%20are%20not%20just%20earning%20by%20selling%20fruit%20but%20also%20tree%20waste.%20Sometimes%2C%20many%20farmers%20do%20not%20accept%20money%2C%20as%20this%20process%20benefits%20them%20in%20clearing%20fields.%20This%20saves%20them%20labour%20costs%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jagat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELeaving%20no%20waste%20behind%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products%20from%20banana%20fibre%20folders%2C%20yoga%20mats%2C%20baskets%2C%20paintings%2C%20cushion%20covers%2C%20coasters%2C%20and%20more.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20maintains%20a%20zero-waste%20approach%20in%20all%20its%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20utilises%20the%20leftover%20pulp%20from%20the%20fibre%20extraction%20and%20processes%20it%20into%20high-quality%20vermicompost.%20Furthermore%2C%20Taruwar%20extracts%20banana%20liquid%20from%20the%20pulp%2C%20which%20serves%20as%20a%20natural%20fertiliser%20rich%20in%20micronutrients%20like%20potassium%20and%20iron.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20everything%20in%20the%20process%20is%20turned%20into%20something%20valuable%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20sustainability%20and%20social%20impact%20has%20garnered%20significant%20traction%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20turnover%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20in%20the%20previous%20financial%20year.%20Every%20month%2C%20the%20startup%20utilises%20up%20to%20600%20kg%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F264157%2Fbanana-fibre-earns-lakhs-waste-business-success-ecofriendly-handicraft%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanana%20fibres%20%3C%2Fa%3Efrom%20waste.%20Through%20offline%20and%20online%20marketing%2C%20it%20has%20established%20its%20customer%20base%20in%20Kerala%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20startup%20also%20converts%20leftover%20pulp%20from%20the%20fibre%20extraction%20into%20vermicompost%20and%20liquid%20fertiliser.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-3-1727440532-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367843%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20startup%20also%20converts%20leftover%20pulp%20from%20the%20fibre%20extraction%20into%20vermicompost%20and%20liquid%20fertiliser.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatyam%2C%20who%20looks%20after%20marketing%20and%20sales%20of%20the%20company%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20able%20to%20develop%20a%20good%20market%20base%20in%20India%20and%20now%20we%20aspire%20to%20enter%20into%20exports.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%2C%20we%20will%20start%20exporting%20to%20other%20countries.%20A%20lot%20of%20companies%20are%20working%20on%20agriculture%20residues%20to%20make%20products%2C%20but%20our%20zero-waste%20approach%20helps%20us%20stand%20out%20in%20the%20market.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJagat%2C%20Satyam%2C%20and%20Nitish%20are%20not%20only%20entrepreneurs%20but%20also%20champions%20of%20sustainable%20innovation%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20a%20greener%20future%20and%20a%20more%20inclusive%20economy.%20Their%20initiative%20showcases%20the%20potential%20to%20create%20positive%20change%20by%20reimagining%20waste%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%20and%20contributing%20to%20the%20circular%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20their%20dedication%20and%20vision%2C%20Taruwar%20demonstrates%20that%20small%20actions%20can%20lead%20to%20significant%20impacts%2C%20inspiring%20others%20to%20embrace%20sustainability%20and%20community%20empowerment%20in%20their%20entrepreneurial%20endeavours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20at%20his%20switch%20from%20the%20corporate%20world%20to%20a%20purpose-driven%20journey%2C%20Jagat%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20family%20was%20hesitant%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20quit%20my%20job.%20After%20you%20invest%20your%20time%20and%20efforts%20in%20pursuing%20higher%20education%20in%20engineering%20and%20an%20MBA%2C%20anyone%20can%20expect%20you%20to%20settle%20for%20a%20high-paying%20job.%20But%20after%20the%20initial%20doubts%2C%20they%20understood%20where%20my%20true%20calling%20was%20and%20extended%20their%20support.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20I%20am%20glad%20that%20banana%20waste%20in%20a%20radius%20of%2010%20kilometres%20from%20our%20factory%20is%20being%20used%20as%20raw%20materials%20for%20useful%20products.%20With%20this%2C%20farmers%20are%20also%20getting%20extra%20monetary%20benefits.%20Banana%20waste%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20headache%20for%20them%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Jagat%20Kalyan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728280003000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-5-1727440520.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D367817%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202021%2C%20three%20college%20friends%20Jagat%20Kalyan%2C%20Satyam%20Kumar%2C%20and%20Nitish%20Verma%20launched%20Taruwar%20Agro%20to%20make%20banana%20fibre%20folder%2C%20yoga%20mats%2C%20baskets%2C%20paintings%2C%20coasters%2C%20and%20more.%20Following%20a%20zero-waste%20approach%2C%20they%20process%20all%20parts%20of%20trees%20%E2%80%93%20from%20leaves%20to%20stems%20and%20pulp%20%E2%80%93%20into%20useful%20products.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F367817%2Fbihar-college-friends-turn-banana-tree-waste-into-useful-products-with-startup-taruwar-agro%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fawad%20Khan%2C%20Vaani%20Kapoor%20Commence%20Romantic%20Comedy%20%E2%80%98Abir%20Gula